<TITLE> PM wants modern, profitable rail sector </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 9 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has stressed modernisation of Bangladesh Railway for profitability, her press secretary said on Monday. "The prime minister has said the rail sector cannot be made profitable with the old infrastructure. To make the sector attractive she emphasised more facilities," Abul Kalam Azad told reporters after a cabinet meeting. The meeting approved three proposed instrumentsthe Saarc Convention on Mutual Assistance in Criminal Matters, the Charter for the Saarc Development Fund and an Inter Governmental Agreement on the Trans Asian Railway Network. The prime minister's press secretary said India had proposed the Convention on Mutual Assistance in Criminal Matters to raise the level of cooperation among member countries. He said the Saarc Development Fund would play a significant role in poverty alleviation, raising standard of living and boosting regional assistance among member countries. The meeting also asked for further scrutiny of a proposed Duty Free Tariff Preference and Letter of Interest of the Indian government. bdnew
